# Bipolar Junction Transistors (BJT)

---

## # NPN Transistor

### Structure

```
N (Emitter) | P (Base) | N (Collector)
```

### Operation

- Electrons injected from emitter into base
    
- Thin base ‚Üí minimal recombination
    
- Reverse‚ÄĎbiased base‚Äďcollector junction sweeps electrons into collector
    
- **Major carriers**: Electrons
    
- **Electron flow**: E ‚Üí B ‚Üí C
    
- **Conventional current**: C ‚Üí E
    

---

## # PNP Transistor

### Structure

```
P (Emitter) | N (Base) | P (Collector)
```

### Operation

- Holes injected from emitter into base
    
- Reverse‚ÄĎbiased base‚Äďcollector junction pulls holes into collector
    
- **Major carriers**: Holes
    
- **Hole flow**: E ‚Üí B ‚Üí C
    
- **Conventional current**: E ‚Üí C
    

---

## # Important Mobility Insight

- Electron mobility {{responseHTML}}gt;$ Hole mobility
- Consequences:
    - NMOS devices smaller than PMOS
    - NPN transistors faster than PNP

